This paper is primarily focused on the task of visual object tracking, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep neural networks and optimization-based methods, which are commonly studied in the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also involves the analysis of video data, which is a common topic in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the security implications of adversarial attacks, which is a topic commonly studied in the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
